articles.title: About this site
articles.description: Some additional details about the website
articles.contents:
Kylie Alberts
I am originally from the San Francisco Bay Area. I obtained my B.S. in Neurscience at Union College, NY. At Union, I also minored in Data Analytics and German. I am a current Ph.D. Candidate at UCLA in Psychology where I study older adults’ susceptibility to falling for scams and fraud. I recently interned at American AgCredit as their 2025 Data Science Intern. Upon graduation, I hope to pursue a career in Data Science so I can discover insights through data and code everyday! In my free time, I love to explore National Parks, read books, and go to concerts.

R Markdown
This is an R Markdown document. Markdown is a simple formatting
syntax for authoring HTML, PDF, and MS Word documents. For more details
on using R Markdown see http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com.
When you click the Knit button a document will be
generated that includes both content as well as the output of any
embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code
chunk like this:
summary(cars)
##      speed           dist       
##  Min.   : 4.0   Min.   :  2.00  
##  1st Qu.:12.0   1st Qu.: 26.00  
##  Median :15.0   Median : 36.00  
##  Mean   :15.4   Mean   : 42.98  
##  3rd Qu.:19.0   3rd Qu.: 56.00  
##  Max.   :25.0   Max.   :120.00
